{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568926,"nonce":"AlKWNN5El9y+MxWgKIoQxOx+GSQ=","kind":"spec","title":"kref output UX paper-cut sweep ŌĆö design"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568926,"nonce":"FLR62YbVhpoAwSGNQJfug70guL4=","body":"# kref output UX paper-cut sweep ŌĆö design\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-18\n**Status:** approved (brainstorming ŌåÆ ready for implementation plan)\n**Scope:** human-readable output across every `kref` command, anchored on the\n`list`/`ls` listing. Introduces one presentation seam, a tier safety signal, a\nglobal `--json` flag, and consistent confirmations.\n\n## 1. Context\n\nA UX pass over the CLI started from one complaint ŌĆö `kref ls` has no header, so\nyou cannot tell what the columns mean, what you can filter on, or which\nvisibility tier an entry lives in. Running the tool live surfaced a wider set\nof paper cuts that share a root cause: there is no presentation layer. Every\ncommand calls `writeJSON(cmd, v)` directly, so the human-vs-machine decision is\nmade ad hoc per command, and the listing renderer hand-pads columns with\n`fmt.Sprintf` and silently drops the `Tier` field the store already computes.\n\nObserved paper cuts:\n\n**`list`/`ls`**\n1. No header row ŌĆö `fdd23cc786c4  memory  open  API key location`; columns\n   (id/kind/status/title) are unlabeled.\n2. Tier column missing ŌĆö entries live in `private`/`personal`/`shared` but the\n   listing never shows which. Security-relevant: you cannot see at a glance\n   what is exposed. `snap.Tier` is populated and then discarded at render time.\n3. No `--tier` filter ŌĆö `store.ListFilter.Tier` exists and works; no CLI flag\n   exposes it.\n4. No row count / summary.\n5. Non-meaningful sort ŌĆö output is DAG-read order, only coincidentally grouped\n   by tier.\n\n**Cross-command consistency**\n6. Split-brain output defaults ŌĆö `add`/`rm`/`restore`/`purge`/`init`/`remote`/\n   `sync`/`ingest` emit JSON by default; `list`/`show` emit human text. No\n   consistent rule.\n7. `add` returns a raw JSON blob (`{\"id\":\"\u003c64 hex\u003e\"}`) where a human wants a\n   confirmation.\n8. `add` hides the tier it used ŌĆö default tier is `personal`, default kind is\n   `document`, never echoed, so you cannot tell a note landed where you meant\n   (security-relevant default).\n9. Inconsistent id width ŌĆö `list` truncates to 12 chars, `show` prints the full\n   64.\n\n## 2. Goals / non-goals\n\n**Goals**\n\n- A single presentation seam so output policy lives in one place.\n- A header row and a colored, glyph-prefixed `TIER` column on `list`, plus a\n  `--tier` filter and a deterministic sort.\n- Human-readable output as the default for every command; machine output behind\n  a single global `--json` flag.\n- Friendly, consistent action confirmations that echo the tier/kind that was\n  actually used.\n- A tier safety signal that survives `NO_COLOR` and piping (glyph, not color\n  alone).\n\n**Non-goals**\n\n- No new output formats beyond human and JSON (no YAML, no `--format`\n  templating, no `--quiet`). YAGNI.\n- No change to any existing JSON shape ŌĆö only the *default* flips.\n- No paging, no interactive TUI, no `--watch`.\n- No change to command structure, names, aliases, or the `--help` grouping\n  (that landed in the prior remediation pass).\n\n## 3. Decisions (locked during brainstorming)\n\n1. **Scope:** full UX sweep across every command, not just `list`.\n2. **Output model:** promote `--json` to a single persistent flag on the root\n   command. Every command defaults to human-readable text; `--json` forces JSON\n   everywhere. Format never auto-switches on TTY ŌĆö piping `kref list` still yields\n   stable human text (matches `gh`/`docker`). Color and headers auto-disable\n   when stdout is not a TTY or `NO_COLOR` is set.\n3. **Tier signal:** a dedicated `TIER` column, color-coded with a leading glyph\n   (`ŌŚÅ` private / `ŌŚÉ` personal / `ŌŚŗ` shared; red / yellow / green). The glyph\n   prints even under `NO_COLOR` or when piped, so the safety signal never\n   depends on color alone.\n4. **Dependencies:** zero new modules. `golang.org/x/term` is already in the\n   tree (indirect) and is promoted to a direct dependency for TTY detection;\n   alignment uses stdlib `text/tabwriter`; color is a tiny internal ANSI helper.\n5. **JSON is frozen:** every existing `--json` payload is byte-for-byte what it\n   is today. Scripts opt into `--json`.\n6. **Sort order:** `list` becomes deterministic ŌĆö tier (private ŌåÆ personal ŌåÆ\n   shared) ŌåÆ kind ŌåÆ title ŌåÆ id.\n7. **id width:** `list` and action confirmations use the shared 12-char\n   `ShortID`; `show` keeps the full 64-char id (it is the detail view and the\n   canonical reference). This inconsistency is intentional, not accidental.\n\n## 4. Architecture ŌĆö one presentation seam\n\n### 4.1 New package: `internal/render`\n\nPure presentation, unit-testable in isolation, imports only `internal/entry`\nand the standard library (`io`, `fmt`, `sort`, `text/tabwriter`). Decoupled\nfrom cobra and from TTY detection ŌĆö callers pass a resolved `color bool`, so\ntests exercise both colored and plain paths with a `bytes.Buffer`.\n\n- `ShortID(id entity.Id) string` ŌĆö canonical 12-char truncation, the single\n  source of truth for short ids (closes #9 for the listing/confirmation\n  surfaces).\n- `Tier(tier string, color bool) string` ŌĆö `\"ŌŚÅ private\"` etc., ANSI-colored\n  when `color` is true, glyph-only when false.\n- `List(w io.Writer, items []*entry.Snapshot, color bool)` ŌĆö header row\n  (`TIER  ID  KIND  STATUS  TITLE`), `text/tabwriter`-aligned rows, a\n  `(deleted)` marker on tombstoned rows, and a trailing `N entries` summary\n  (`no entries` when empty).\n- `Show(w io.Writer, snap *entry.Snapshot, color bool)` ŌĆö the detail view,\n  preserving the current `ID [tier/status] Title ŌĆö by Name \u003cemail\u003e\\n\\nBody`\n  format, with the tier badge colored when enabled. Full id retained.\n- `Action(w io.Writer, verb string, snap *entry.Snapshot, color bool)` ŌĆö a\n  one-line confirmation, e.g. `added ŌŚÅ shared a5745cf90565  spec  \"Auth flow\n  spec\"`. Used by `add`, `rm`, `restore`, `purge`, `init`, `remote set`, `sync`.\n\nSorting lives in `internal/render` next to `List` (see ┬¦6) so the rendered\norder is the decided order.\n\n### 4.2 cobra glue: `cmd/kref/output.go`\n\n- `emit(cmd *cobra.Command, human func(io.Writer, bool), jsonValue any) error`\n  ŌĆö if `jsonMode(cmd)`, call the existing `writeJSON(cmd, jsonValue)`\n  (unchanged); otherwise run `human(cmd.OutOrStdout(), useColor(cmd))`.\n- `jsonMode(cmd) bool` ŌĆö reads the root persistent `--json` flag.\n- `useColor(cmd) bool` ŌĆö `!jsonMode(cmd) \u0026\u0026 term.IsTerminal(int(os.Stdout.Fd()))\n  \u0026\u0026 os.Getenv(\"NO_COLOR\") == \"\"`. Color keys off the real stdout fd while\n  writing to `cmd.OutOrStdout()`; under `go test` the fd is not a terminal, so\n  test output is deterministic and uncolored.\n\nThe root command (`main.go`) gains `root.PersistentFlags().BoolVar(\u0026asJSON,\n\"json\", false, \"machine-readable JSON output\")`. Per-command `--json` flags are\nremoved in favor of the inherited persistent flag.\n\n## 5. Behavioral changes per command\n\n| Command | Default today | Default after (human) | `--json` |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `list`/`ls` | unlabeled cols, no tier | header + `TIER` glyph column + `N entries`; new `--tier` filter; deterministic sort | unchanged array |\n| `add` | `{\"id\":\"\u003c64hex\u003e\"}` | `added ŌŚÅ shared a5745cf90565  spec  \"Title\"` (echoes tier+kind) | unchanged |\n| `ingest` | JSON results array | per-file lines + `N ingested, M quarantined, K failed` summary | unchanged |\n| `rm` / `restore` / `purge` | JSON status | one-line confirmation (`tombstoned ŌŚÅ shared a5745cf90565`, etc.) | unchanged |\n| `remote set` / `sync` | JSON status | one-line human status | unchanged |\n| `show` | full id, human | unchanged + tier badge color when enabled | unchanged |\n| `init` | JSON | human confirmation (author, tier note) | unchanged |\n\n`ingest`'s human summary still returns the same non-zero exit on failed files;\n`purge`'s confirmation prompt and `--force`/`--gc`/`--push` flags are untouched\nŌĆö only the post-action JSON line becomes a human line under the default mode.\n\n## 6. Sort order\n\n`list` output becomes deterministic. The comparison key is tier rank\n(private = 0, personal = 1, shared = 2) ŌåÆ kind ŌåÆ title ŌåÆ id. The sort is applied\nin `internal/render.List` (operating on the slice the store returns) so the\nstore's iteration order does not leak into the UI. Putting it in render keeps\n`store.List` a thin query and gives the sort a unit test that does not need a\ngit repo.\n\n## 7. Error handling\n\nNo new error paths. `--tier` reuses `parseTier`, returning the existing\n`invalid --tier %q (want private|personal|shared)` error. `term.IsTerminal` and\n`os.Getenv` cannot fail. tabwriter writes propagate the underlying writer's\nerror, which `emit` returns like any other.\n\n## 8. Testing\n\n- **`internal/render` unit tests** (no git repo needed): header present; tier\n  glyph present with `color=false`; ANSI codes present with `color=true` and\n  absent with `color=false`; `(deleted)` marker; `N entries` / `no entries`\n  summary; sort determinism across a shuffled input; `ShortID` width and\n  short-input safety.\n- **`cmd/kref` CLI suite**: the JSON-capturing helper(s) append `--json` so the\n  existing 31 JSON assertions keep exercising frozen shapes. New specs: `list`\n  default emits a header and a tier column; `list --tier shared` filters;\n  `--json` still emits the array; `add` default prints a confirmation echoing\n  the tier; `NO_COLOR=1` output contains the glyph but no ANSI escape.\n- **Docs:** README `list`/output examples and CHANGELOG updated. No new flags\n  documented beyond `--json` (global) and `list --tier`.\n\n## 9. Blast radius\n\n- `internal/render`: new package.\n- `cmd/kref/output.go`: new file (emit/jsonMode/useColor).\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go`: each RunE swaps its `writeJSON` tail for `emit`; `list`\n  gains `--tier`; per-command `--json` flags removed.\n- `cmd/kref/main.go`: root gains persistent `--json`.\n- `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`: JSON helper passes `--json`; new human-output specs.\n- `go.mod`: `golang.org/x/term` indirect ŌåÆ direct.\n- `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`: output examples + changelog entry."}]}